------------------------------------------------------------------
KEY LESSON
------------------------------------------------------------------

Metadata fields are a low-effort, high-reward hiding spot in
steganography challenges. Always run exiftool as one of your
first moves on any image. Look for fields that are unusually
large or contain data that does not match what the field is
supposed to hold. Hex encoding is one of the most common ways
to hide binary data in a text metadata field -- convert it with
xxd -r -p and check what file type emerges.
